args: All this fun in the sun is exhausting.\nI think I need a rest.
Even while resting, it will be difficult\nto stay cool in this heat.

And ever since, it's said that you can\nhear a low, sad voice coming up from\nthe depths of the sea...
THE TERRIFYING VOICE OF THE\nLONG-HAIRED LADY!
Well? What did you think?\nAnyone need to change their pants?
You suck at telling stories, man.\nI've heard lullabies that were scarier!
Are you all right, Julietta?\nYou look pale.
N-not at all! I am perfectly fine.\nNever felt better, in fact.
Julietta, look out! There's a\nlong-haired woman behind you!

So you WERE scared!\nYou should have just said so!
Only a child would be scared by such a\nthird-rate, hackneyed story! I could see\nthe ending coming from a mile away.
Bold words! But what say you prove\nthis bravery with a test of courage?
That's right. I recently discovered an\neerie cave near here that's pitch black\neven in the middle of the day.
You will go into its depths and leave\na rock there to prove you made it.
Then, once you're back, we'll go in after \nto confirm the veracity of your claim.
A test of courage during the day?\nWhat manner of a coward do you\ntake me for, madam?!
This will be a simple matter!
Ha ha ha! That's the spirit!\nNow let's get going.
Hmm. I see what she meant about this\nparticular cave being eerie.
*shudder* Well, let us be done with this\nnonsense and get shed of this place.
Hee hee! She'll never imagine that\nwe're already in here ahead of her!
Asking someone to wander into a cave\nand place a rock there isn't a test of\ncourageâ€”merely an errand!
They need obstacles getting in their way,\nwhich we are going to provide! And so...
Eeek! D-did I just hear a voice?
Hee hee! I got her! Okay, now it's\nyour turn, {player_name}.
You want ME to scare Julietta?
That girl is as nervous as a long-tailed\ncat in a room full of rocking chairs.\nWe need to toughen her up!
So come on, {player_name}!\nShe's counting on you!
All right, let me give it a try. *ahem*\nWho goes...um...theeere?
Eeeek! A-all right, I DEFINITELY\nheard something that time...
THAT half-hearted mumble scared her?\nLame, man. Laaaaaame.
All right, let's keep this up!
I took a bunch of cold, slimy seaweed\nand hung it from a fishing pole.\nNow we juuuust...
Eeek! I just felt something\ncold on my neck!
Next, I'm going to inflate this paper bag,\nthen pop it with a BANG!
Ha! We're on a roll now!
You are WAY too into this.
Well, Julietta IS giving her\nthe reactions she wanted...
*sniff* Okay, this is as far in as you can go.\nJust put the stone down and then you can\nrun out of here very, very quickly.
Hee hee! I hope she's ready\nfor the final test!
She'll let her guard down as soon as she\ndrops the stoneâ€”and that's when I strike!
I don't know. I think she's scared enough.

That's why I must turn my heart to stone\nand terrify her. It's for her own good!
All right, she put the rock down.
Finally! Now I can go back to...
Uh, guys? I think she fainted standing up.\n...Which I did not know was a thing!
I knew you were overdoing it.
Ack! Someone start compressions!\nSomeone start CPR!
